## Tab 2 — Dashboard (Strategic Synthesis)

### Empty State

Displayed when a founder visits the Dashboard tab before any synthesis has been generated.

Layout: Placeholder wireframe blocks representing the six content blocks — visually present but empty and muted. An overlay card sits centered on the page with:
- Headline: "Your Strategic Synthesis will appear here"
- Body: "Complete your Vision State to generate your Clarity Compass synthesis — a north star document that codifies your trajectory, surfaces structural implications, and articulates what you are ultimately building."
- CTA button: "Go to Vision State" — navigates to the Vision State tab

This same empty state displays on return visits before submission.

---

### Synthesis Dashboard — Loaded State

Six content blocks rendered in sequence. All content is AI-generated via n8n and GPT except Block 1 which is deterministic. Content is read-only — no editing in this view.

---

#### Block 1 — Vision Header

Deterministic — pulled directly from stored data, no GPT generation.

Displays:
- Agency name
- Version name (as set in the submit block)
- Date generated
- A one-line characterization of the ultimate vision — derived from the combination of Field: Underlying Drive + Field: What the Business Ultimately Becomes
- Horizon Scenario Strip — a horizontal visual strip showing all three horizons. Each horizon tile displays: horizon label, tagged scenario name (or "No scenario tagged"), GVI score (if available), and GVI band label (if available). Styled as compact tiles in a row.

---

#### Block 2 — Movement 1: The Declared Trajectory

GPT-generated prose block.

**Purpose:** Narrative spine of the synthesis. Tells the three horizons and ultimate vision as a single progressive arc — not horizon by horizon but as a continuous story of what is being built and where it is going.

**Format:** Three to four paragraphs of flowing prose. No bullet points. No subheaders within this block.

**Tone:** Confident and declarative. Peer-level. Observational.

**Block header:** "Your Declared Trajectory"

**Display note:** Full-width prose block. Subtle left border accent in brand color to visually distinguish from the structural blocks around it.

---

#### Block 3 — Trajectory Visual Strip

Deterministic — built from stored intake data.

A horizontal timeline display showing the progression across all four horizons. Each horizon is a card in the sequence showing:
- Horizon label
- Two to three of the most strategically significant field selections from that horizon — chosen by a deterministic rule set (not GPT): for each horizon, surface the primary endgame or identity field plus the most revealing success marker selection
- Tagged scenario GVI band if available — displayed as a small colored band badge

Cards are connected by a directional arrow or line to reinforce the arc visually.

**Display note:** This is a visual summary element, not a data dump. Maximum three data points per horizon card. Design must be clean and shareable — this block travels well when the document is exported or shared.

---

#### Block 4 — Movement 2: The Structural Implications

GPT-generated hybrid block — prose plus callout statements.

**Purpose:** Surfaces what the declared trajectory structurally implies. Not prescriptive — observational characterizations of what a path of this nature requires.

**Format:** Two to three paragraphs of prose followed by two or three standalone callout statements. Callout statements are visually distinct from the prose — displayed as highlighted quote-style blocks.

**Callout statement format:** Each begins with a stem phrase generated by GPT — something like "A trajectory of this character implies..." or "The path you've described requires..." followed by the specific implication.

**Block header:** "What This Path Implies"

---

#### Block 5 — Movement 3: What This Reveals

GPT-generated insight block.

**Purpose:** The synthesis's most distinctive contribution. Surfaces one or two observations that emerge from reading all declarations together — things the founder couldn't see from inside the form.

**Format:** One or two insight blocks. Each insight block contains:
- A specific generated headline — GPT has full latitude to name this. Should be specific and personal, not generic category labels. Guardrail: headline should be a phrase or short sentence that characterizes the insight, not a label.
- Two to three sentences of supporting narrative unpacking the observation and why it is structurally significant.

**Block header:** "What the Full Picture Reveals"

**Display note:** This block should feel visually distinct from the others — slightly elevated design treatment to signal that this is the synthesis's deepest layer of insight.

---

#### Block 6 — Movement 4: The North Star Statement

GPT-generated closing block.

**Purpose:** A single synthesized statement of what the founder is ultimately building and why it matters. The document's closing artifact.

**Format:**
- The North Star Statement itself — one to three sentences maximum. Displayed in large type, visually dominant, centered or prominently styled.
- Two lines of supporting context below the statement — what this north star represents and what the journey toward it is ultimately in service of.

**Block header:** "Your North Star"

**Display note:** This block needs visual weight. Large type for the statement. Clear white space around it. Designed to be screenshot-able and shareable as a standalone artifact.

