## Data and Save Logic

- Auto-save triggers on every field selection change — saves to draft record in Supabase
- Save button within each horizon section performs an explicit save of that horizon's current state
- Draft record is upserted until Submit is triggered — no duplicate records created during drafting
- Submit fires the n8n workflow with the full intake payload — creates a new immutable version record
- Version record stores: all field selections, all scenario tags, version name, timestamp, generated synthesis JSON
- Each horizon's scenario tag is stored as a foreign key reference to the saved GVS scenario record
- Synthesis JSON is stored as a structured object with named fields corresponding to each of the six blocks — Block1Header, Block2Trajectory, Block3VisualData, Block4Implications, Block4Callouts, Block5Insights, Block6NorthStar

---

## n8n Workflow Trigger

On Submit:

1. Collect full intake payload — all field selections across all four horizons
2. Collect scenario data for any tagged horizons — GVI score, band, composition label, pressure profile, GPT synthesis from the scenario record
3. Collect Agency Snapshot baseline data
4. Package into structured JSON payload
5. Send to n8n webhook
6. n8n constructs GPT prompt using the four-movement brief and the full payload
7. GPT returns structured JSON with all generated blocks
8. n8n writes the synthesis JSON to the version record in Supabase
9. Frontend receives confirmation and renders the Dashboard

